<TEXT>
president alfredo cristiani in 
his first full day in office called friday for a regional effort 
to end his nations leftist revolution and said it was as crucial 
as dismantling the nicaraguan rebels 
also friday insurgents denied they owned a huge arms cache 
displayed as materiel captured from rebels the exhibition is 
psychological warfare they said 
jose napoleon duarte the staunch us ally who retired after 
five years as president traveled to washington for cancer 
treatment friday duarte 63 is dying of liver cancer 
and the armys monthly duty orders published friday show a key 
clique of colonels consolidated its power 
cristiani leader of the rightist arena party gave a press 
conference in the presidential palace 
he said the nineyear salvadoran revolution is a regional 
problem and should be dealt with in the context of the 1987 
esquipulas ii regional peace plan 
under the plan the five central american presidents agreed in 
february to promote the demobilization of contra rebels based in 
honduras 
cristiani acknowledged the contra plan has a head start we 
have no problem with that going ahead but we would like to see 
equal treatment given to the salvadoran problem and progress there 
too 
he reiterated accusations that nicaraguas leftist regime helps 
arm the salvadoran rebel farabundo marti national liberation front 
nicaragua says it provides only moral support to the guerrillas 
known as fmln 
