hundreds of iranian exiles left the united 
states during the past year and went to iraq to join the fight 
against ayatollah ruhollah khomeinis regime leaders of irans 
main resistance group said friday 
about 1000 antikhomeini iranians rallied outside the united 
nations in a demonstration organized by the washingtonbased 
peoples mujahedeen holy warriors of iran 
there has been a power struggle in iran to select a successor to 
khomeini the nations 86yearold spiritual leader who is 
recuperating in a tehran hospital from abdominal surgery 
mujahedeen leaders said irans ecomony is in a shambles after 
the eightyear war with iraq and government repressions continue 
with hundreds of executions 
it proves khomeinis regime has no chance to stay in power 
said 30yearold parvanah of irvine calif who declined to give 
her last name to protect relatives still in iran 
she said khomeini is the hitler of our generation and i am 
going to fight him along with her 31yearold husband toraj they 
have two daughters 5 and 10 years old 
she said she and her husband would join the iraqbased national 
liberation army the fighting arm of the peoples mujahedeen and 
expected to meet friends who had already joined that force 
i know personally dozens of them from orange county calif 
who went to iraq to fight khomeinis government she added 
i will do anything that they need of me anything to help the 
national liberation army free my people and overthrow khomeini 
