<TEXT>
a federal narcotics agent was charged with 
drug trafficking friday after he said spirits forced him to become 
involved with a sect of drugsmuggling ritual killers 
salvador vidal garcia alarcon 39 a federal judicial police 
officer told authorities his involvement with the sect was limited 
to witchcraft and had nothing to do with drugs or the gruesome 
murders uncovered at a ranch in matamoros in april 
vidal garcia arrested earlier this week pleaded innocent to 
the cocaine trafficking charge in the 7th federal criminal court in 
mexico city conviction can bring a penalty of seven to 25 years in 
prison 
vidal garcia was not charged in connection with the murders or 
other crimes alleged against the sect led by adolfo de jesus 
constanzo a 26yearold cubanamerican who died may 6 in a 
shootout when police raided his hideout in mexico city 
the indictment filed friday charges vidal garcia with the theft 
of 44 pounds of cocaine from a dentist in the western city of 
guadalajara last year he constanzo and constanzos righthand man 
allegedly stole the cocaine in a complicated scam that involved 
posing as us drug agents 
vidal garcia is one of several police officers mentioned by cult 
members during interrogation but deputy attorney general javier 
coello trejo said friday that vidal garcia is the only federal 
agent involved with the cult 
we are cleaning house said coello head of the attorney 
generals narcotics division 
coello refused to discuss statements by the sects alleged high 
priestess sara aldrete villareal that the late mexican head of 
interpol the international police agency was also involved in the 
cult 
several members of the gang including ms aldrete told 
authorities that vidal garcia used his position on the federal drug 
task force to provide protection to the smugglers 
ms aldrete also said that constanzo told her he killed two men 
as a favor to vidal garcia their bodies were later discovered at 
the matamoros ranch 
when vidal garcia was questioned by fellow federal police agents 
after the gangs arrest he admitted knowing constanzo and other 
cult members but denied any wrongdoing he said his relationship 
with constanzo and the others was limited to religious matters 
vidal garcia said he had been possessed by three spirits since 
birth he said the spirits were useful in his witchcraft but that 
when they took hold of him it could be violent and painful 
officials declined to say whether the officer will be able to 
remain on the force while his case is pending 
constanzo and his followers were the targets of massive manhunts 
on both sides of the usmexico border set off by the discovery of 
horribly mutilated bodies buried at the matamoros ranch 
among the victims was mark kilroy a 21yearold university of 
