ecstasy in the clandestine lab he said a nationwide search was 
under way for ms pineda trindad the alleged leader who was 
believed to be about 50 years old and had led the life of an 
affluent businesswoman 
the second gang also based in guadalajara was led by a 
colombian named jaider curiel choles the deputy attorney general 
said he described curiel choles as the principal medellin cartel 
contact in mexico 
federal judicial police arrested curiel choles and 16 others in 
a series of raids this week coello said conficating 35 pounds of 
cocaine a house in guadalajara several bank accounts two 
vehicles and several weapons 
he said the gang trafficked in marijuana and lsd as well as 
