<TEXT>
the way some observers see it the shares of 
general motors corp are about to send out a warning that the stock 
markets strong 1989 rally might soon run out of gas 
the analysts in question are followers of the gm bellwether 
indicator one of the many traditional tools developed over the 
years to try to outguess the direction of stock prices 
the theory holds that gm stock must set a new high within four 
months of its previous peak in any given market cycle to maintain 
an all clear signal for investors if it fails to do so then 
it switches to a bearish or at least caution indicator 
the all clear light has been on since oct 20 1987 the day 
after the crash on black monday notes robert stovall of 
stovalltwentyfirst advisers inc long known as a leading 
advocate of the gm bellwether 
but barring some lastminute fireworks stovall says that is 
about to change 
gms most recent peak was 4744 adjusted for a subsequent 
2for1 split on feb 8 1989 the shares trading late last week 
around 41 would have to rally above their february level by 
thursday june 8 to avoid a negative signal 
of course many money managers of the investment institutions 
that dominate the modern markets dismiss indicators like the gm 
bellwether as quaint artifacts of a bygone time like engraved 
stock certificates or mechanical tickertape machines 
if they want an indicator thank you theyll take a 
computerprogram model combining dozens of variables that suggests 
changes in their tactical asset allocation plans 
still says stovall the gm bellwether has been an accurate 
guide about 70 percent of the time since the 1920s and has some 
logic going for it 
gms stock is a useful foreshadower of future market trends 
because of its giant capitalization and cyclical product line he 
maintains it is also the only blue chip stock to have over many 
years regularly raised or lowered its dividend depending on the 
corporate outlook 
besides say some other analysts its a potential sign of 
trouble any time you see big names like international business 
machines and gm lagging behind when the market is rallying 
gms action is especially disturbing since it looks so toppy 
and vulnerable on the chart and in addition has proved to be so 
very important as a forecasting tool says stan weinstein in the 
current edition of his investment advisory letter the professional 
tape reader 
however closely wall streeters may watch it gm stock has been 
only a fringe participant at best in the markets rise to new highs 
in the 1980s 
actually said stovall the shares have been better as 
directional signals than as an investment over the past 20 years 
gm shares at the 40 level are virtually unchanged from the 
1969 price zone while merck has soared by eight times ford stock 
has risen by a factor of five and ibm has more than doubled among 
many other superior longterm performers 
</TEXT>
