<TEXT>
longterm interest rates plunged to their lowest 
levels in 15 months friday as investors snapped up bonds in flurry 
of anticipation that the federal reserve might ease credit 
following a weak us employment report 
it was a spree a jamboree a jubilee said robert brusca 
chief economist at nikko securities co international inc 
trading started with a bang after the labor department reported 
the nations unemployment rate dipped to 52 percent in may from 
aprils 53 percent 
although lower unemployment can indicate stronger economic 
growth which tends to boost interest rates the market 
concentrated on factors in the report that underscored the view 
that the economy is slowing for example the report indicated may 
had the weakest monthtomonth job growth since march 1986 
the report sent bond prices sharply higher and the gains held 
throughout the session 
the treasurys bellwether 30year bond soared 1 points or 
nearly 1875 per 1000 in face amount its yield which moves in 
the opposite direction plunged from thursdays 860 percent to 
843 percent its lowest since march 3 1988 
the report accentuated rumors all week that the fed is going 
to ease interest rates said robert chandross vice president and 
chief economist for lloyds bank plcs north america head office in 
new york 
the question is whether the market is expecting more than its 
going to get he said 
indications that the economy was slowing and thus dampening 
inflation have raised speculation the federal reserve might push 
interest rates lower to help curb the recent rise of the dollar 
chandross suggested the fed may allow the federal funds rate 
the interest on overnight loans between banks to trade lower the 
fed influences the fed funds rate and thus other shortterm 
interest rates by adding money to the banking system or draining 
it out 
the federal funds rate traded at 9 916 percent late in the 
session down from 9 1316 percent late thursday 
a lower federal funds rate could entice major banks to lower 
their prime interest rates a benchmark used to set interest in a 
variety of consumer and corporate credit early friday southwest 
bank of st louis lowered its prime rate from 115 percent to 11 
percent but major banks did not follow suit 
if we do get some prime rate cuts by the large money center 
banks it tells the fed that demand for money has weakened a 
little and the fed will seriously consider cutting the discount 
rate said jack barbanel senior vice president at gruntal amp co 
while some experts speculated a widespread prime rate cut could 
come as early as next week they said they did not believe the fed 
would ease credit by cutting its discount rate the interest it 
charges on loans to banks as quickly 
in the secondary market for treasury securities prices of 
shortterm governments rose 2332 point to 1 points intermediate 
maturities jumped 1 points to 1 points and 20year issues were 
up a full point according to telerate inc the financial 
information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
