maturity fell to 739 percent from 743 percent late thursday 
yields on threemonth treasury bills slipped to 862 percent as 
the discount fell 23 basis points to 835 percent yields on 
sixmonth bills fell to 856 percent as the discount fell 26 basis 
points to 812 percent yields on oneyear bills fell to 855 
percent as the discount fell 22 basis points to 793 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
