<TEXT>
sun microsystems inc completing 
an expensive bonebybone transplant of the skeleton of the 
company and plagued by supply problems thursday forecast 
significantly lower earnings or possibly a loss in its fourth 
quarter ending june 30 
a loss would be its first since it reported red ink in its 
initial quarter in 1982 
although sun a leader in workstation computers issued its new 
forecast at the close of the stock market its share price tumbled 
125 to 2075 in trading on the nasdaq overthecounter market 
revenues in the fourth quarter could fall below the 497 million 
of the third quarter ended march 30 the company said that would 
put the companys fiscal 1989 revenues at about 18 billion up 
from 12 billion last year 
the conversion to a new management information system in april 
was not without difficulties the company said this slowed 
production early in the quarter in addition the introduction in 
this quarter of five major new products has made it more difficult 
to forecast product mix 
sun said production of the new products has been somewhat 
impaired by an insufficient supply of certain components 
scott mcnealy suns president declined to specify which 
components were in short supply but said we expect those 
component shortages to not be an issue by midjuly 
he also declined to say which of the companys new products were 
affected most by the supply shortage or to give details of how well 
the products were selling but he said the sparcstation1 suns 
lowcost entry into the workstation market with a starting price of 
about 9000 was clearly the lead product among the new 
entries 
mcnealy said the company could be faulted for not being more 
precise on our forecasting but he said it was difficult to 
predict what customers would order and how much the change in 
management information systems would affect sales 
basically we had to do a bonebybone transplant of the 
skeleton of the company he said referring to the replacement of 
a management information computer system that had been in place 
since its early days with a new system 
delays have also resulted from continued strong sales of suns 
traditional products causing unexpected production demands the 
company said 
these factors have hindered suns ability to assess accurately 
the companys incoming orders to forecast and to schedule 
production efficiently the company said 
sun said the problems will be confined to the fourth quarter and 
the company is not encouraging changes in expectations for fiscal 
1990 which the company said will be an excellent year 
kathleen hurley an analyst at the san josebase research firm 
dataquest inc said she was not surprised by the companys 
announcement in light of the ambitious product introductions made 
this year 
when they announced the sparcstation i thats a significant 
revamping she said that affected their net income it takes a 
lot of time and money to do that 
she called the cost of introducing the new products and the 
multimilliondollar change of the management information system a 
natural migration i dont think they messed up 
i think theyll recover by the end of the first quarter of 
fiscal 1990 or the start of the second quarter she said the 
workstation market as a whole is doing well 
